go_data.term: vascular endothelial growth factor receptor signaling pathway
go_data.justification: The ANGPT2-TIE2 tyrosine kinase pathway is implicated in primary lymphoedema.
ANGPT2 is considered an antagonist of ANGPT1-induced TIE1-TIE2 signalling in the vascular system, and Angpt2 knockout mice have disrupted postnatal angiogenic remodelling.
The ANGPT2-TIE2 tyrosine kinase pathway is involved in the formation and remodelling of lymphatic vessels.
Tie2 is described as a receptor tyrosine kinase.
